results.name: Smallest number having exactly s divisors, where s is the n-th semiprime (A001358).
comment: This is to smallest integer for which the number of divisors is the n-th prime (A061286) as semiprimes (A001358) are to primes (A000040). - _Jonathan Vos Post_, Feb 03 2011
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jul 15 2004
